<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 5:49AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Armstrong County
through 615 AM CDT...
At 549 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Palo Duro Canyon, or 15 miles southwest of Claude,
moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Claude, Washburn and Wayside.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
